<section>
  <p>
    Have you found it’s hard to find folks having meaningful discussion about Mobile Development (iOS, Android, Window Phone, Mobile Web) in Madison? Wouldn’t it be great to join a community of people who recognize the explosion of mobile devices and see how they are affecting our interactions? What if we could pull together locals and invite some experts from around the country and have that conversation in Madison?
  </p>

  <p>
    This community exists in Madison and its members are quietly shaping the future of devices and apps that you rely on every day. We’re bringing them together under one roof for two days in the middle of the winter in Wisconsin because we know there isn’t much to do between New Years and Memorial Day.
  </p>
  <h5>Winter? In Wisconsin?</h5>
  <p>Yep. If the white stuff scares you, you <em>could</em> stay inside for the duration event, the venue and hotel are connected. Additionally, there are four restaurants, a bowling alley, a rock climbing wall, Ice cream shop, and Live Music both nights of the event. Our organizers have orchestrated two years of <a href="http://madisonruby.org">Madison Ruby</a> and added a new knockout event in 2012 called <a href="http://uxmad.com">UXMad</a> and know how to deliver a good time while building an inspiring and enlightening program. Venue rooms are limited so, <a href="http://www.union.wisc.edu/wuhotel-reservations.htm">book your room at the Wisconsin Union Hotel</a> today and use our group code: SNOWMOBILE.</p>
